I've spoken to management at this restaurant many times in hopes they'd course-correct on their own but they show no signs that they care so I'm finally just gonna give them the bad review they seem to want. This restaurant has been in the neighborhood for a long time and perhaps that's made them complacent. First off I tend to only order from them on seamless because I don't speak Spanish and there is massive confusion of the "who's on first base? What's his name is on 2nd base" variation. Which has resulted in me getting the completely wrong order several times. How hard is it to find and hire ONE bilingual person in SPANISH HARLEM? that would solve half their problems. But alas, their menu on seamless is also flawed (try ordering a large chicken soup which comes out to about 20 dollars (which I've also informed management about on numerous occasions) but yesterday was the last straw. I had just gotten out of the hospital for emergency dental work and needed some soft food. So I placed an order with them. Shortly after encountering the chicken soup issue I called them and told them not to charge me 20 dollars for it. They said they'd refund me the excess money (which they haven't thus far) them I get a call from the delivery guy that's he's 5 mins away, come down and get my food. This annoys me since I'm just out the hospital which is the reason I ordered in the 1st place. They're in the neighborhood, if i felt up to the task of walking around I would've picked up my food myself. I am, after all paying for the convenience of delivery. To make matters worse I bite the bullet and go outside (in the cold) and wait for 20 mins. Called the delivery guy back and got no answer. All of This is especially ridiculous when you account for tipping, taxes and delivery fees. DO YOUR JOB AND DELIVER TO MY DOOR. NOT MY NEIGHBORHOOD, NOT MY BLOCK, NOT THE CORNER. get a bike lock, lock your bike up and bring the food to your customer. IF I ever order from you again, and your delivery guy tells me to come downstairs I'm going to tell him "ok ill be right down " and then proceed to order from someone else while he waits in the cold like I did.

Please read before ordering. I would give them no stars but the lowest is 1. Where do i begin, My order came 2 hours after being ordered. When it arrives the delivery guy asks for more than what was told to me over the phone. When I ask for the receipt he gives me an attitude. On the receipt I see the price was written over my original price. I tell him that the price is wrong and I'm going to call the store to verify. He then says "you don't want food? Ok" and leaves. When I call the store they leave me on hold then when I call back and ask for the manager the guy gets an attitude with me and hangs up. If you want excellent spanish food and excellent service order from  Caridad right across the street. I will never order from Sandy's ever again.

Whether you are going to dine in or take out, you better pay attention to how your food is prepared. On tuesday evening I went to dine in with my two friends. They each ordered a meal of spanish rice with chicken and I ordered a meal of tostones ( fried plantains) with chicken.  When the meal arrived, there was a piece of hair in my chicken. I immediately notified the waitress and she was hesistant to exchange it but eventually did. When she returned with a different chicken plate, it was cold. The meal that my friends ordered was also cold. A person sitting next to us ordered water and there was a fly in it. When she complained, all the waitress said was " oh! it must have fallen into it" and showed no major concern. Overall a horrible experience and my best friends and I will not be returning to this restaurant.
